[[File:Mati Laur.jpg|thumb|Mati Laur in 2010.]] '''Mati Laur''' (born 17 June 1955 in [[Abja-Paluoja]]) is an [[Estonia]]n [[historian]]. He has written and co-authored many textbooks about early modern [[Estonia]]. He has published a number of scholarly articles about eighteenth-century Estonia, which also was the subject of his Ph.D. thesis. Despite this narrow specialisation, he is professor of [[general history]] at the [[University of Tartu]].
Together with [[Karsten Brüggemann]], Laur is editor of the historical journal [[Forschungen zur Baltische Geschichte]] [Research on Baltic history].
