'''The Rolling Stone Interview''' is a feature article in the American magazine ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' that sheds light on notable figures from the worlds of music, popular culture, or politics. Editor [[Jann Wenner]] has said that the interview is "part[ly] based on ''[[The Paris Review]]'', which featured definitive interviews with writers like [[Ernest Hemingway]] and [[John Steinbeck]], exploring their lives, their philosophy and their technique".{{citation needed|date=August 2012}}
Subjects of the interviews have ranged from former presidential candidate [[John Kerry]] to the landmark December 1970 interview with [[John Lennon]]. ''The Rolling Stone Interviews: 1967–1980: Talking With the Legends of Rock and Roll'' (1989, {{ISBN|0312034865}}) is a collection of significant interviews from the magazine's first 15 years.
