'''Tiverikoto''' (Tivericoto) is an extinct and poorly attested [[Cariban language]]. [[Terrence Kaufman]] placed it with [[Yao language (Trinidad)|Yao]] in his Yao group.<ref>{{cite book | title=Atlas of the World's Languages | publisher=Routledge | last=Kaufman |first=Terrence |editor1-first=Christopher |editor1-last=Moseley |editor2-first=R.E. |editor2-last=Asher | year=1994 | location=New York | pages=73–74 | isbn=0-415-01925-7 }}</ref>
