'''Vasile Grecu''' (31 July 1885 – 27 May 1972) was a [[Romania]]n [[philologist]] and Byzantinist.
He became a corresponding [[list of members of the Romanian Academy|member of the Romanian Academy]] in 1936. Between the years 1938-1947, he was a professor at the [[University of Bucharest]]. Grecu's works include critical editions of the works of the Greek historians [[Doukas (historian)|Doukas]], [[Kritoboulos of Imbros]], [[George Sphrantzes]] and [[Constantine Porphyrogenitus]].
== References == * Waldemar Ceran, "Grecu Vasilije", ''Encyklopedia kultury bizantyńskiej'' (Warsaw: Oktawiusz Jurewicz, 2002), p.&nbsp;189.
